<para id="RM0000015W100RX" category="C" type-id="302GI" name-id="AX038-13" from="200601">
<dtccode>P2716</dtccode>
<dtcname>Pressure Control Solenoid "D" Electrical (Shift Solenoid Valve SLT)</dtcname>
<subpara id="RM0000015W100RX_01" type-id="60" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___000061600000">
<name>DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>The linear solenoid valve (SLT) controls the transmission line pressure for smooth transmission operation based on signals from the throttle position sensor and the vehicle speed sensor. The ECM adjusts the duty cycle of the SLT solenoid valve to control hydraulic line pressure coming from the primary regulator valve. Appropriate line pressure assures smooth shifting with varying engine outputs.</ptxt>
<ptxt>(*): Duty Ratio</ptxt>
<ptxt>The duty ratio is the ratio of the period of continuity in one cycle.</ptxt>
<ptxt>For example, if A is the period of continuity in one cycle, and B is the period of non-continuity, then</ptxt>
<ptxt>Duty Ratio=A/(A + B) x 100(%)</ptxt>
<table pgwide="1">
<tgroup cols="3" align="center">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="0.82in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="3.15in"/>
<colspec colname="COL3" colwidth="3.11in"/>
